[5] Cholera - Ghana
Date: Sun, 22 Jan 2006
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Ghanaweb.com [edited]
<http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/artikel.php?ID=97986>

A cholera outbreak at Domeabra in the Ahafo-Ano South District has claimed
the life of the Zonal Coordinator of the National Disaster Management
Organization (NADMO).
About 28 others have been admitted to the Domeabra Health Center and the
Mankranso Government Hospital. Briefing the Ghana News Agency Mr Johnson
Kwaku Adu, the Ahafo-Ano South District NADMO Co-ordinator, attributed the
outbreak to poor sanitation and contaminated water in the town. He said the
only stream that serves the people as drinking water has been polluted by
garbage that is washed into it during the rainy season.
Mr Adu said a task force was constituted to educate the people on the
importance of environmental hygiene and how to treat and prevent the
disease from spreading when it spread and killed 2 people at Domeabra and
Wioso.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
